    {
      "type": "Feature",
      "properties": {
        "record": "BA-202602665",
        "address": "431 PAGE AVE NE, ATLANTA GA 30307",
        "status": "ACA Pending",
        "date": "06/11/2026",
        "description": null,
        "owner": "CARNES DOROTHY J",
        "tree_dbh": "46",
        "tree_location": "see site map",
        "reason_removal": "Other",
        "tree_description": "Numbered flagging tape Reason for Removal:OtherComments: The tree has a codominant structure at the base with\napproximately 8 ft of included bark. Multiple other codominant\nunions are consistent throughout the canopy. The tree is growing\nagainst a fence. On the north side at the fence, the roots appear to\nhave been severed at some point in the past. Sounding of that\nside of the tree was hollow and shell failure occurred during\ninspection, exposing advanced decay at the root flare and lower\ntrunk. A small opening between the root flares on the west side led\nto a larger internal cavity. Endoscopic inspection indicates internal\ndecay. Video uploaded to Accella showing sounding, probing, and\nendoscopic inspection.\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\tTree number:2Species:Pecan Tree Size (DBH):29Tree location:see site map Description of Tree:Numbered flagging tape Reason for Removal:OtherComments: In the upper crown, one of the codominant leaders shows a\nconglomerate of irregular woundwood forming a pronounced C\nshaped wound margin, with woundwood wrapping broadly around\nthe union. From the property to the south looking north, the last\nphoto shows this union is sharply codominant with included bark\nand suggests this portion may have broken off or been topped at\none time.",
        "tree_number": "1",
        "species": "Pecan"
